fstests-utils adhoc <test> [test...]

Run the listed tests in parallel across whatever workers are currently
up.  No build, no provision, no teardown, no digest -- just dispatch and
print the results.  Use this to:
  - reproduce a flake on the existing fleet
  - re-check a specific fix against the same kernel
  - validate the parallel retry path on idle hosts during a serial run

Env:
  WORKERS   worker backend (default local-vm)
  TIMEOUT   per-test timeout (default 30m)
  HOSTS     explicit comma-separated subset of hosts (default: $B/list)
            e.g. HOSTS=fstests@1.2.3.4,fstests@5.6.7.8
